WEBVTT

00:02.309 --> 00:04.004
Here's to God‐‐

00:04.046 --> 00:05.506
in ten years from now, Street,

00:05.506 --> 00:06.632
good friends
living large in Texas.

00:06.673 --> 00:07.633
Is it true, Mr. Street?

00:07.674 --> 00:09.343
That I love Lyla Garrity?

00:09.384 --> 00:11.970
(announcer)
Street the only one
to be able to get to him.

00:12.012 --> 00:14.181
That's a gigantic hit
on Street.

00:14.181 --> 00:15.974
(announcer)
...Quarterback.
no one's seen this guy‐‐

00:16.016 --> 00:17.184
(coach)
Start throwin' the ball.

00:17.184 --> 00:19.520
Hey, boy, how you doing?
Doing good.
How are you doing?

00:19.520 --> 00:20.479
Well, I'm hanging
in here, man.

00:20.521 --> 00:22.523
(Taylor)
Your dad in Iraq‐‐
that must be hard.

00:22.564 --> 00:24.358
Did you forget to take
your pills yesterday?

00:24.358 --> 00:25.359
No.

00:25.400 --> 00:26.944
(man)
Looked like she wandered

00:26.985 --> 00:27.986
into a neighbor's house
around the block.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.863
Is she all right?
Found her taking a bath.

00:29.905 --> 00:31.073
They said it's dementia.

00:31.114 --> 00:33.534
She's okay now?
She's fine.
She's grandma, you know?

00:33.575 --> 00:35.202
Jason's paralyzed.

00:36.411 --> 00:37.871
(Jason)
My legs are never
gonna get better.

00:37.913 --> 00:39.414
You and me,
we're not getting married.

00:39.456 --> 00:40.958
Don't say that, Jason.

00:42.000 --> 00:43.210
(Lyla)
What happened with us

00:43.210 --> 00:45.045
came from all these feelings
about Jason.

00:45.045 --> 00:48.382
Is something happening
between you and Riggins?
No!

00:48.423 --> 00:49.716
You don't steal
a cripple's girl.

00:49.716 --> 00:51.051
You're a coward, Riggins!

00:51.051 --> 00:52.344
(Joanne Street)
Welcome home.

00:54.221 --> 00:56.974
You are all that I have
in the whole world.

00:57.015 --> 00:59.059
All I have.

01:10.404 --> 01:12.030
[beeping]

01:12.072 --> 01:14.032
[Tom Petty's
Saving Grace]

01:14.074 --> 01:17.703
♪ Oh, the ground
that no one owns ♪

01:17.744 --> 01:21.081
♪ Past statues that atone ♪

01:21.123 --> 01:22.457
♪ For my sins ♪

01:25.043 --> 01:28.338
♪ There's a guard
on every door ♪

01:28.380 --> 01:31.091
♪ And a drink on every floor ♪

01:31.091 --> 01:35.721
♪ Overflowing
with a thousand amens ♪

01:38.098 --> 01:41.101
♪ And it's hard to say ♪

01:41.101 --> 01:43.437
♪ Who you are these days ♪

01:43.478 --> 01:45.105
Come on.

01:45.147 --> 01:48.108
♪ But you run on anyway ♪

01:48.108 --> 01:50.402
♪ Don't you, baby? ♪

01:52.404 --> 01:54.614
Where's my Nevermind CD?

01:54.614 --> 01:57.451
I don't know.
Did you leave it in your room?

01:57.451 --> 01:59.578
No, I didn't leave it
in my room!

01:59.619 --> 02:02.622
It should be right here
with the rest of Nirvana.

02:02.664 --> 02:03.832
Can you get it off
of the computer?

02:03.832 --> 02:05.959
No!
I can't get it on my computer!

02:06.001 --> 02:07.753
I just‐‐
I just‐‐

02:07.794 --> 02:09.129
I wanna listen to it,

02:09.129 --> 02:11.632
and I want the CD,
and I want it right now.

02:11.673 --> 02:13.300
I don't understand
why this is something

02:13.342 --> 02:15.093
to get so upset over.

02:15.135 --> 02:17.596
Because I'm crippled,
and I wanna listen to Nirvana!

02:17.638 --> 02:19.306
Is that so hard
to understand?

02:19.348 --> 02:21.099
Huh?

02:23.644 --> 02:27.147
I'll just have to get myself
another one.

02:27.147 --> 02:30.150
Sweetheart, the record store
is like four miles away.

02:30.150 --> 02:32.277
Well,

02:32.319 --> 02:34.488
I better get goin'.

02:36.156 --> 02:39.493
♪ You keep runnin'
for another place ♪

02:39.493 --> 02:42.663
♪ To find that saving grace ♪

02:45.540 --> 02:48.043
♪ Don't ya, baby? ♪

03:03.642 --> 03:07.187
[soft pop in background]

03:07.229 --> 03:14.695
♪ ♪

03:30.085 --> 03:32.170
You can find
Clay Aiken under A.

03:38.176 --> 03:39.636
Like he's not
your boyfriend.

03:39.678 --> 03:42.389
Hey, what Clay and I have
is special, okay?

03:42.389 --> 03:44.182
America loves him,
and so do I.

03:44.224 --> 03:46.226
You just need to start
respecting that.

03:46.226 --> 03:48.562
Why don't you send me
an invitation to the wedding?

03:48.603 --> 03:50.856
I would, but it's just
gonna be the two of us

03:50.897 --> 03:54.234
and, uh, a harpist.

03:54.276 --> 03:56.194
[laughing]
And, uh, Ryan Seacrest

03:56.236 --> 03:57.863
is gonna perform
the ceremony.

03:57.904 --> 03:59.322
Nice.

04:07.956 --> 04:09.207
Hi.

04:09.249 --> 04:10.292
Hi.

04:10.292 --> 04:11.501
[giggles]

04:16.923 --> 04:18.592
How are you?
Great.

04:18.592 --> 04:20.177
And you?

04:20.218 --> 04:22.220
I'm okay.

04:22.262 --> 04:23.263
(Melissa)
Jason, hi.

04:23.263 --> 04:25.265
Lyla, we gotta go.

04:25.265 --> 04:26.516
We're gonna
be late for class.

04:26.558 --> 04:28.602
You gotta go.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.645
Unless I don't.

04:35.942 --> 04:39.446
I know we have
a lot to talk about.

04:39.446 --> 04:40.614
Maybe‐‐

04:40.614 --> 04:42.783
Yeah, yeah.
We should go somewhere.

04:42.783 --> 04:45.452
[Spoon's
I Turn My Camera On]

04:45.494 --> 04:47.621
♪ I cut my fingers
on the way ♪

04:47.662 --> 04:48.955
How do we do this?

04:48.997 --> 04:51.500
I'm not really sure.

04:51.500 --> 04:52.626
♪ The way
you're slippin' away ♪

04:52.626 --> 04:55.128
♪ I turn my feelings off ♪

04:55.170 --> 04:56.463
♪ You made me
untouchable for life ♪

04:56.463 --> 04:58.548
What if I put my leg
on your shoulder?

04:58.590 --> 05:00.801
(Street)
Higher up.
Come on, here!

05:00.801 --> 05:02.511
[laughing]

05:03.970 --> 05:05.388
Okay, okay.
I got an idea.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.974
Hop off.

05:07.974 --> 05:09.226
♪ Get up
Roll it out ♪

05:09.267 --> 05:11.269
♪ Keep on
showing 'em out ♪

05:11.311 --> 05:12.646
♪ You hit me like a Tom ♪

05:12.646 --> 05:14.314
[grunts]

05:14.356 --> 05:16.233
[laughing]

05:16.274 --> 05:17.442
You okay?

05:17.484 --> 05:18.443
I'm fine.

05:18.485 --> 05:20.237
I'm fine.

05:20.278 --> 05:21.863
I'm good, I'm good.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.534
Stop gawking at me
and come here.

05:31.039 --> 05:33.708
♪ I turn my camera on ♪

05:33.708 --> 05:37.003
♪ I cut my fingers
on the way ♪

05:37.003 --> 05:39.005
♪ On the way,
on the way ♪

05:39.005 --> 05:40.841
♪ I feel me slippin' away ♪

05:40.841 --> 05:42.342
♪ I wipe my feelings off ♪

05:42.384 --> 05:44.845
It's okay.

05:44.845 --> 05:47.305
It's okay.

05:51.351 --> 05:53.019
I‐‐I can't.
Lyla, stop.

05:53.019 --> 05:55.897
I can't feel anything.

06:58.351 --> 07:00.920
Ma'am, look, it's just‐‐

07:00.920 --> 07:02.589
Yeah, I know that Medicare‐‐

07:02.589 --> 07:04.424
Medicare says that
they'll pay for all that,

07:04.424 --> 07:06.217
but for some reason,
I have this bill

07:06.259 --> 07:09.179
saying that I owe $348.

07:09.220 --> 07:10.221
Matthew?

07:10.263 --> 07:13.266
Matthew, have you got
that leaky faucet fixed yet?

07:13.266 --> 07:14.267
Um, yeah, I know‐‐

07:14.267 --> 07:15.602
Get your dad
to help you.

07:15.602 --> 07:18.438
Grandma, Dad's in Iraq,
remember?

07:18.438 --> 07:19.564
Hmm.
So, look, what I'm really

07:19.606 --> 07:23.276
trying to figure out here
is if we can maybe arrange

07:23.276 --> 07:24.277
some kind of
in‐home visits or something...

07:24.277 --> 07:25.320
He's out front.
Go help him.

07:25.362 --> 07:27.614
if, you know, Medicare
will pay for that as well.

07:27.614 --> 07:29.783
[car door closes]

07:29.783 --> 07:32.786
Can‐‐can you hold on
one sec?

07:32.786 --> 07:34.746
Go help him
with his bags.

07:34.788 --> 07:36.790
All right.
I'm gonna go look, okay?
Yeah.

07:42.629 --> 07:44.589
Dad?

07:47.634 --> 07:49.386
Matt.

07:50.470 --> 07:51.554
You're home!

07:52.931 --> 07:54.724
You're home!
You're home.

07:57.477 --> 07:59.896
(team)
P‐A‐N‐

07:59.938 --> 08:01.898
T‐H‐

08:01.940 --> 08:04.943
E‐R‐S.

08:04.984 --> 08:06.486
Bring it in, guys.

08:06.486 --> 08:07.904
Bring 'em in, guys!

08:07.946 --> 08:08.905
Let's go, let's go!

08:08.947 --> 08:12.450
Listen up‐‐perfection
is the order of the day.

08:12.492 --> 08:13.827
Anything else
is unacceptable, understood?

08:13.827 --> 08:14.911
(team)
Yes, sir.

08:14.953 --> 08:16.329
We leave the mistakes

08:16.329 --> 08:17.539
up to the Westcott Warriors.

08:17.539 --> 08:18.540
Also, First Baptist is having

08:18.581 --> 08:21.334
their annual Panther
dinner on Thursday night,

08:21.334 --> 08:22.168
so be there.
[boys groaning]

08:22.210 --> 08:24.337
Uh‐uh, uh‐uh.
I don't wanna hear it.

08:24.337 --> 08:27.257
(Taylor)
You'll have your jackets.
You'll have your ties.

08:27.298 --> 08:28.800
There's gonna be
no foul language.

08:28.842 --> 08:30.927
You're not gonna make
jackasses out of yourself.

08:30.969 --> 08:33.346
Don't embarrass me.
Don't embarrass the school.

08:33.346 --> 08:34.597
Understood?
(team)
Yes, sir.

08:34.639 --> 08:36.266
All right, coach,
break it down.

08:36.307 --> 08:37.350
(boy)
Come on, let's hit it!

08:37.350 --> 08:38.685
[overlapping shouts]

08:38.685 --> 08:40.311
One, two, three!

08:40.353 --> 08:41.521
Can't lose!

08:41.521 --> 08:42.605
Miss Levine told me

08:42.647 --> 08:45.358
that you're in real trouble
in her English class.

08:45.358 --> 08:48.528
Yeah, well, why don't we just
put me into an easier class?

08:48.528 --> 08:50.363
That's not really
the problem, is it?

08:50.363 --> 08:53.324
I hear you got an oral report
due this week.

08:53.366 --> 08:55.368
You started reading
that book yet?

08:55.368 --> 08:57.370
Uh, no, I haven't,

08:57.370 --> 08:59.581
but I am
lookin' forward to it.

08:59.581 --> 09:01.833
You get help
on your homework, Tim?

09:01.875 --> 09:04.377
Maybe from
the Rally Girls sometimes?

09:04.377 --> 09:05.545
No.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.380
Never.

09:07.380 --> 09:09.049
Not once.

09:09.049 --> 09:10.216
Uh, you know,

09:10.216 --> 09:12.635
that Scarlet Letter paper
that y'all wrote‐‐

09:12.677 --> 09:15.805
I mean, Julie was up all night
long writing that one.

09:15.847 --> 09:18.391
Did‐‐did you write that one?
Oh, yeah.

09:18.391 --> 09:19.392
You did?
Yep.

09:19.392 --> 09:20.518
Oh!
Could I see it?

09:23.396 --> 09:26.316
Wow, "Modern Themes
in The Scarlet Letter."

09:26.357 --> 09:28.068
A‐.
Look at that.

09:28.068 --> 09:30.403
What's The Scarlet Letter
about, Tim?

09:30.403 --> 09:32.530
You know
what it's about.

09:32.572 --> 09:34.407
I do know.
Yeah.

09:34.407 --> 09:36.534
What's The Scarlet Letter
about?

09:37.577 --> 09:40.538
It's about, uh,
a gal that, uh,

09:40.580 --> 09:42.123
named Scarlet,
obviously‐‐

09:42.123 --> 09:43.875
[exhales]
Tim,

09:43.917 --> 09:45.418
you did not write
this paper.

09:45.418 --> 09:47.420
What's the big deal?

09:47.420 --> 09:49.422
Well, the big deal is
that it's part of my job

09:49.422 --> 09:51.508
to make sure that
you don't grow up stupid.

09:51.549 --> 09:53.426
It's bad for the world.

09:53.426 --> 09:55.428
[snickers]
That's not funny, Tim.

09:55.428 --> 09:57.555
That is not funny.

09:57.597 --> 09:59.432
So you know what‐‐I'm making it
my personal responsibility

09:59.432 --> 10:01.601
to make sure that you don't
get any more free passes

10:01.601 --> 10:03.394
from your teachers.

10:03.436 --> 10:05.897
From here on in, you're gonna
sink or you're gonna swim,

10:05.939 --> 10:08.441
based on you,
based on your work.

10:08.441 --> 10:09.442
You get me?

10:09.442 --> 10:11.945
We're two wins away
from playoffs, Mrs. Taylor.

10:11.945 --> 10:13.613
I appreciate that.

10:13.613 --> 10:14.948
The timing of this
couldn't be worse.

10:14.948 --> 10:16.366
Well, I'm sorry.

10:16.407 --> 10:18.535
I don't pass,
I don't play.

10:18.576 --> 10:22.664
Well, then, I think
we'd better get you to pass.

10:22.664 --> 10:24.999
Yep!
Yeah!

10:24.999 --> 10:26.459
Oh, yeah!
Yeah, baby!

10:26.459 --> 10:28.378
Mike Jones

10:28.419 --> 10:30.588
for the ladies,
baby, yeah!

10:30.630 --> 10:32.465
Good Lord,
that boy's good.

10:32.465 --> 10:33.466
Herc.

10:33.466 --> 10:34.592
Hmm?

10:34.634 --> 10:35.927
How do I have sex?

10:37.804 --> 10:40.473
Oh, my goodness.
My boy's growin' up.

10:40.473 --> 10:41.641
No, seriously.

10:41.641 --> 10:43.143
I just need
a little information.

10:43.143 --> 10:45.645
I kinda had a...

10:45.645 --> 10:48.606
a little‐‐
a little mishap, if you will.

10:48.648 --> 10:50.483
Mishap?

10:50.483 --> 10:52.485
Yeah.
By yourself
or with a girl?

10:52.485 --> 10:53.778
With a girl.

10:53.820 --> 10:55.113
[chuckling]

10:55.155 --> 10:57.157
I just‐‐
I was having trouble, uh‐‐

10:57.157 --> 10:59.617
I was having trouble...

10:59.659 --> 11:01.828
staying at attention.

11:01.828 --> 11:03.663
You know what I mean?

11:03.663 --> 11:05.540
I do know
what you mean,

11:05.540 --> 11:07.208
but I'm proud of you
anyway.

11:07.208 --> 11:09.836
Where'd you find her?
It's not important.

11:09.836 --> 11:11.504
I didn't catch
that name.

11:11.504 --> 11:13.506
Who was this again?

11:13.506 --> 11:14.507
It was Lyla.

11:14.507 --> 11:15.675
Come on.

11:15.675 --> 11:16.676
No!

11:16.676 --> 11:19.012
Boo!
Uh‐uh!

11:19.012 --> 11:21.014
What‐‐
what are you sayin' to me?

11:21.014 --> 11:23.016
Well, of course
your ding dong went soft.

11:23.016 --> 11:24.642
It was tryin'
to protect you.
I know, I know.

11:24.684 --> 11:27.520
All right, it wasn't,
like, my proudest moment,

11:27.520 --> 11:30.023
but, you know, if you'd
hold back on the judgment

11:30.023 --> 11:31.858
just a little bit right now,
that'd be great.

11:31.858 --> 11:33.693
'Cause this is really
helping me right now.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.612
I know what you want.
I know what you want.

11:35.653 --> 11:37.530
You wanna grab her
and do her, huh?

11:37.530 --> 11:39.532
Make her forget about
that other guy, right?
Yes.

11:39.532 --> 11:41.201
Just bang
the bejesus out of her.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.494
Exactly.
That's exactly what I wanna do.

11:43.536 --> 11:44.871
Yeah.
Not gonna happen.

11:44.871 --> 11:46.664
Least not for a while,
anyway.

11:50.210 --> 11:52.629
Why not?

11:52.670 --> 11:54.714
Dude, you're like
a newborn baby.

11:54.714 --> 11:56.716
You don't know how
to do anything.

11:56.716 --> 11:59.719
Look, man, whatever
worked for you before

11:59.719 --> 12:01.721
may not work now,
you know?

12:01.721 --> 12:04.891
You just gotta figure out
what turns you on, you know?

12:04.891 --> 12:07.727
Like, will I ever
be able to‐‐

12:07.727 --> 12:09.020
What, shoot fireworks?

12:09.062 --> 12:10.730
Yeah.
Have a super happy
fun time?

12:10.730 --> 12:11.564
Yeah.
Yes.

12:11.606 --> 12:14.108
Probably.
Just maybe not every time.

12:16.527 --> 12:18.071
Look,

12:18.071 --> 12:21.741
nothing's like it was,
you know?

12:21.741 --> 12:24.244
But don't look
so glum, man.

12:24.244 --> 12:27.205
There's more to life
than hit it and quit it, QB,

12:27.247 --> 12:28.248
trust me.

12:31.751 --> 12:33.002
[chuckling]

12:33.920 --> 12:34.921
(Tami)
Landry.

12:34.921 --> 12:36.714
Landry.
Hi.

12:36.756 --> 12:38.675
How you doing?

12:38.716 --> 12:39.717
Good.

12:39.759 --> 12:40.468
Do you know
Tim Riggins?

12:40.510 --> 12:42.053
He's lookin' for
an English tutor,

12:42.095 --> 12:44.097
and I think you would
be just perfect.

12:44.097 --> 12:45.598
Do you?

12:45.598 --> 12:47.767
Yeah, I do, and I just
want you to know

12:47.767 --> 12:50.228
that he wants to really
improve his grades.

12:50.270 --> 12:52.105
He's looking
to expand his mind.

12:52.105 --> 12:53.731
Don't go easy on him.

12:53.773 --> 12:55.233
Spend as much time
as you need.

12:55.275 --> 12:57.610
Do whatever you need to do,
and y'all get in there

12:57.610 --> 12:59.028
and get it goin'.

12:59.070 --> 13:00.780
And I think you'll be great.
Thanks, Landry.

13:00.780 --> 13:01.781
Okay, um‐‐

13:01.781 --> 13:03.700
Good luck.

13:03.741 --> 13:05.118
Okay.

13:05.118 --> 13:06.744
[whistle blows]

13:07.787 --> 13:09.289
Go!

13:13.293 --> 13:14.752
Set!

13:15.795 --> 13:17.088
Hut!

13:20.133 --> 13:21.718
(Taylor)
There it is.

13:21.759 --> 13:23.136
That's nice, Matt.

13:23.136 --> 13:24.220
That's nice.

13:29.142 --> 13:30.601
Set.

13:30.643 --> 13:31.978
(Crowley)
Coach Taylor,
you seen this?

13:31.978 --> 13:33.229
Huh?

13:33.271 --> 13:34.814
Texas Football magazine.

13:34.814 --> 13:37.650
Top ten high school coaches
in the state of Texas.

13:37.650 --> 13:39.652
You're on this list.

13:39.652 --> 13:41.320
Right there, Coach.
Oh, there's no livin'
with him now.

13:41.320 --> 13:44.782
Better watch what you say.
Says "up and coming."

13:44.824 --> 13:46.325
How 'bout that?

13:46.367 --> 13:48.619
(Crowley)
Coach, we're getting T‐shirts
with that on it.

13:48.661 --> 13:50.663
It'll be on the radio.
(McGill)
Sweaters.

13:50.705 --> 13:52.373
That's a three‐minute break.
Three minutes.

13:52.373 --> 13:53.374
Let's go!

13:53.374 --> 13:54.834
[whistle blows]

13:57.295 --> 13:59.005
Hey, Dad.

13:59.005 --> 14:00.757
Lookin' good, Matt.
Thanks.

14:00.798 --> 14:03.009
I think I'm gonna take off.
I got some sleep to catch up on.

14:03.009 --> 14:05.011
Wait, can you hold on
a minute?

14:05.011 --> 14:07.013
I want you to meet the coach.
Hey, come here, come here.

14:07.013 --> 14:08.806
This is my dad.

14:08.848 --> 14:10.183
Coach!

14:10.183 --> 14:11.684
Yeah.

14:11.684 --> 14:14.145
Uh, this is my dad,
Henry Saracen.

14:14.187 --> 14:16.022
This is Coach Taylor.
This is my dad.

14:16.022 --> 14:17.857
How do you do?
Pleasure to meet you.

14:17.857 --> 14:18.858
(Taylor)
Pleasure to meet you.

14:18.858 --> 14:20.860
You're, uh,
you're on leave?

14:20.860 --> 14:23.029
Yeah, he's home
for two weeks.

14:23.029 --> 14:24.822
That's good‐‐you gonna get to
see your son play a little bit?
I hope so.

14:24.864 --> 14:27.617
He's done a hell of a job
leading this team, I tell you.

14:27.658 --> 14:28.826
Not too much trouble
from him, huh?

14:28.868 --> 14:31.162
He's a little bit of trouble.
He's not too much trouble.

14:31.204 --> 14:32.914
A little bit of trouble,
huh? He's gotta be.

14:32.914 --> 14:34.916
He's been a pleasure to teach,
I can tell you that.

14:34.916 --> 14:37.794
I didn't know
he had it in him.

14:38.878 --> 14:40.338
(Taylor)
He's got plenty in him.

14:40.379 --> 14:42.173
He's been a good team leader
out here.

14:42.215 --> 14:44.634
I'll tell you what.
You can be proud of your son.

14:44.675 --> 14:46.052
Just hope he keeps doin'
okay under pressure.

14:46.052 --> 14:47.678
(Taylor)
You betcha.

14:47.720 --> 14:49.889
Well, I gotta run, Coach.
I'll talk to you later.

14:49.889 --> 14:51.057
It was a pleasure
to meet you.
Very nice meeting you.

14:51.057 --> 14:52.725
I'll see you
at home, Son.

14:52.725 --> 14:54.060
Yeah, I'll see you
at home, Dad.

14:54.060 --> 14:55.895
Thanks‐‐thanks, Coach.

14:55.895 --> 14:56.988
