any porn.

16:53.804 --> 16:55.890
No, Jason, wait!

16:57.141 --> 16:59.477
Listen,
I know this is weird,

16:59.518 --> 17:00.978
but we can
get through this.

17:01.020 --> 17:02.813
That's not what I'm‐‐

17:02.855 --> 17:03.940
I think we were
really close before.

17:03.981 --> 17:05.650
It's not about sex.

17:05.691 --> 17:08.611
And a lot of couples
have very good luck

17:08.653 --> 17:10.029
in the shower.

17:10.071 --> 17:12.865
You wanna get laid
that bad, call Riggins.

17:18.037 --> 17:19.538
(Landry)
You know what?

17:19.580 --> 17:21.082
I don't know
about you, Tim,

17:21.123 --> 17:24.043
but I am excited
about your new journey

17:24.043 --> 17:26.379
into the wonderful world
of American literature.

17:26.420 --> 17:27.588
I really, really am.

17:27.630 --> 17:30.550
What do you think of the name
Crucifictorious?

17:30.550 --> 17:33.010
I wanted to go with
Stigmatalingus,

17:33.052 --> 17:35.471
but I, uh, got outvoted.
They're both crap, Landry.

17:35.513 --> 17:36.847
I mean, that's great.

17:36.889 --> 17:37.765
You are entitled
to your opinion.

17:37.807 --> 17:39.976
That's just what makes
America so great.

17:40.017 --> 17:41.978
Just being honest.

17:42.019 --> 17:44.564
Okay, Of Mice and Men.

17:44.564 --> 17:46.566
The good news is it's a short
book‐‐it's a hundred pages,

17:46.566 --> 17:48.734
so you can pretty much
rock it out in one night.

17:48.776 --> 17:50.486
Right on that.

17:52.405 --> 17:54.865
Oh, my God,
you can't read, can you?

17:54.907 --> 17:56.075
Is that it?

17:56.075 --> 17:58.536
You're one of those kids who
just slipped through the cracks?

17:58.578 --> 18:00.705
I can read, you joke.

18:00.746 --> 18:02.623
I just choose not to.

18:02.665 --> 18:04.709
That's cute.
That's real cute.

18:07.420 --> 18:10.590
(Landry)
I got a show
y'all might wanna come to.

18:10.631 --> 18:12.508
(Saracen)
Still like it
almost burnt?

18:12.550 --> 18:13.593
Yes, sir.
There you go.

18:13.634 --> 18:14.677
Look at that.

18:14.719 --> 18:16.429
It's good, Matthew.
Thanks.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.556
Beats the hell out of
them MREs.

18:19.557 --> 18:20.308
[tapping fork]

18:20.349 --> 18:22.059
(Mrs. Saracen)
Is that one done?

18:22.101 --> 18:23.102
Oh, yeah, it's done.

18:23.144 --> 18:27.940
[continues tapping]

18:27.940 --> 18:30.026
Relax.

18:30.067 --> 18:32.236
What is she
so nervous for?

18:32.278 --> 18:35.072
She's always like this‐‐that's
what I was trying to tell you.

18:35.114 --> 18:37.742
That's why I wanna try
and get a nurse in here

18:37.783 --> 18:39.035
or something like that.

18:39.076 --> 18:40.745
[tapping]
I'm not nervous.

18:40.786 --> 18:41.996
I‐‐I know.

18:42.038 --> 18:44.832
So, what's it, um,

18:44.874 --> 18:47.752
wh‐what's it like
over there in Iraq?

18:47.793 --> 18:49.128
Good.
Building schools.

18:49.128 --> 18:50.630
Doing a lot of good.

18:50.671 --> 18:52.923
Yeah, so when do you think
it's gonna be over?

18:52.965 --> 18:55.593
When do you think you can
come home for‐‐for good?

18:55.635 --> 18:57.720
I tell you this‐‐
we're not gonna leave

18:57.762 --> 18:59.722
until those people
have a stable government.

18:59.764 --> 19:01.974
You know, uh,

19:01.974 --> 19:04.727
there's some people
who think that we should just,

19:04.769 --> 19:07.563
you know, get everybody
out of there and come home.

19:07.605 --> 19:08.939
Do you know what would
happen if we left?

19:08.981 --> 19:11.108
How many innocent
people would die?

19:11.150 --> 19:13.903
We're gonna stay until we
finish what we started, Matt.

19:13.944 --> 19:16.614
Well, I'm not really saying‐‐
I wasn't saying anything.

19:16.656 --> 19:19.825
I just, you know, I just
like it when you're home.

19:25.706 --> 19:27.124
[horn honks]

19:28.876 --> 19:29.960
Hey, I got you.

19:30.002 --> 19:31.796
No, I got it.
Come on, now.

19:31.837 --> 19:33.005
I already dragged
the other one out here.

19:33.005 --> 19:34.924
I can drag
this one out too.

19:34.965 --> 19:37.134
You're gonna do the last 3 feet
and take all the credit for it?

19:37.176 --> 19:39.095
I'm not gonna give you
the credit now.

19:39.136 --> 19:40.137
I got the other one out‐‐
Hey‐‐

19:43.182 --> 19:45.184
[laughs]

19:45.184 --> 19:47.645
I can't believe
you just did that.

19:47.687 --> 19:50.147
I didn't do anything.
Look at that!

19:50.189 --> 19:51.982
Come on, just‐‐
That's a disaster.

19:52.024 --> 19:53.693
I'll get it.
I'll get it.

19:53.734 --> 19:55.111
Let me ask you something.

19:55.152 --> 19:57.196
Did you, by chance,
make it your personal mission

19:57.196 --> 19:59.949
to take over the education
of Tim Riggins?

19:59.990 --> 20:01.033
I am, actually, yes.

20:01.033 --> 20:02.827
You know, I found out

20:02.868 --> 20:04.870
that he's been having
the Rally Girls do his homework

20:04.870 --> 20:07.039
for I don't know how long.

20:07.081 --> 20:08.916
That's very nice of you,
but we both are aware

20:08.958 --> 20:11.043
of the no pass,
no play policy.

20:11.085 --> 20:12.878
Yeah, I'm very aware
of that, mm‐hmm.

20:12.920 --> 20:13.796
And if you would
just think about this...

20:13.838 --> 20:15.715
I know that
you're not about to say...

20:15.756 --> 20:16.716
if just for
the next couple games.

20:16.757 --> 20:17.758
what I think
you're about to say,

20:17.800 --> 20:18.676
because you know what
the answer is gonna be.

20:18.718 --> 20:20.553
Baby, we've got
a chance at the playoffs.

20:20.594 --> 20:21.887
'Cause you know what?
He's been cheatin',

20:21.887 --> 20:23.556
honey, and I don't
even want to ask you

20:23.556 --> 20:24.557
if you knew that
he's been cheating.

20:24.598 --> 20:25.641
But he's been cheating,

20:25.683 --> 20:27.017
and I know you don't want me
to turn my back on that.

20:27.059 --> 20:28.686
No, I didn't know
he was cheating,

20:28.728 --> 20:31.063
and I know how important
the kid's schooling is.

20:31.063 --> 20:32.982
What I'm saying is that
the next couple of games‐‐

20:33.023 --> 20:34.859
Do you, though? You think
it's as important as winning?

20:34.900 --> 20:36.068
I mean, really, do you?

20:36.110 --> 20:37.278
You're really asking me
that question?

20:37.319 --> 20:39.363
You're asking me that question?
Can you answer the question?

20:39.405 --> 20:41.198
No, I can't answer
the question,

20:41.240 --> 20:42.867
because you won't
let me finish talking.

20:42.908 --> 20:43.784
Well, you know what,

20:43.826 --> 20:45.703
it does not do Tim Riggins
a bit of good

20:45.745 --> 20:47.580
to grow up ignorant
and mean and dumb.

20:47.621 --> 20:48.664
What are you talking about?

20:48.706 --> 20:49.582
That's what you are encouraging
with these boys.

20:49.623 --> 20:51.250
I'm not encouraging that.
Yes, you are!

20:51.292 --> 20:53.085
I know how important
his education is.

20:53.127 --> 20:54.378
No, you're making 'em
feel like

20:54.420 --> 20:56.005
what this town
makes 'em feel like,

20:56.046 --> 20:57.923
which is that football
is the most important thing.

20:57.965 --> 21:00.718
If we send that message to him,
that's what he's gonna believe.

21:00.760 --> 21:02.094
You've gotta be
kidding me.
No, I'm not.

21:02.094 --> 21:03.721
You gotta be kidding me.
I'm not kidding you.

21:03.763 --> 21:05.181
You know I'm not
kidding you.

21:05.222 --> 21:07.224
[cell phone rings]
I can't believe that we're
even disagreeing about this.

21:07.266 --> 21:09.727
I can't believe you're even
asking me to do that.

21:09.769 --> 21:10.853
Hello.

21:10.895 --> 21:12.104
Coach Taylor.

21:12.146 --> 21:12.897
Yeah.

21:12.938 --> 21:14.231
I'll get the rest
of the garbage.

21:14.273 --> 21:17.276
Hey, Coach.
Yes, sir.

21:21.947 --> 21:25.159
Well, I mean, I can't make
any commitments, obviously‐‐

21:29.121 --> 21:30.998
Well, sure.

21:30.998 --> 21:33.083
All right, well, I'll look
forward to your call.

21:33.125 --> 21:36.253
You can consider the
conversation open, of course.

21:36.295 --> 21:38.964
All right, you too.

21:39.006 --> 21:40.966
Thanks, Coach.

21:44.345 --> 21:46.138
What?
Who was that?

21:49.850 --> 21:52.144
That was the assistant coach
from over at UT.

21:52.144 --> 21:56.315
They wanted to know
if I had any interest

21:56.357 --> 21:58.859
in quarterback coach
next season.

21:59.985 --> 22:01.111
Uh‐uh.

22:03.322 --> 22:04.657
That's what the man said.

22:04.698 --> 22:06.075
Nuh‐uh.
Really?

22:06.116 --> 22:08.327
Get outta here!

22:08.327 --> 22:09.995
You're full of it!
Really?

22:10.037 --> 22:11.632
Really?
Yep.

22:15.376 --> 22:16.752
(Landry)
Hey, Riggins.

22:16.794 --> 22:19.338
Hey, Riggins,

22:19.338 --> 22:20.923
when do you
want to get together

22:20.965 --> 22:22.591
and work on that
book report?

22:22.633 --> 22:24.760
Oh, man,
I haven't read that.

22:24.802 --> 22:26.011
Why have you not
read it?

22:26.053 --> 22:28.097
I don't know.
I didn't get around to it.

22:28.138 --> 22:30.140
Okay, just checking.
That's great.

22:30.182 --> 22:34.812
Um, you know if you don't pass,
you don't play, right?

22:34.854 --> 22:35.688
What do you want me to do?

22:35.688 --> 22:36.689
