what happened, honey.

23:53.432 --> 23:54.516
Why is he mad at me?

23:54.558 --> 23:56.018
He's not.
He's just scared.

23:56.060 --> 23:57.102
All right?

23:57.102 --> 23:59.063
We were all just scared,
all right?

23:59.104 --> 24:00.606
What happened?

24:00.606 --> 24:02.191
It's all right.
It's all over, okay?

24:02.232 --> 24:04.526
You all right?

24:04.568 --> 24:06.612
It's not your fault,
okay?

24:09.239 --> 24:12.618
The Medicare is not gonna
pay for at‐home care

24:12.660 --> 24:14.870
unless she has a definitive
diagnosis of Alzheimer's.

24:14.912 --> 24:17.748
Well, let's get her
a diagnosis, then.

24:21.669 --> 24:23.087
What about a home?
What?

24:23.128 --> 24:25.756
My veterans' benefits
should cover that.

24:25.798 --> 24:27.591
(woman)
Yeah, there's some
homes in the area.

24:27.633 --> 24:29.259
But she's Matt's
legal guardian.

24:29.301 --> 24:31.804
If she's in a home,
that's not gonna work.

24:32.972 --> 24:34.765
There's another option.

24:34.807 --> 24:37.768
Mr. Saracen, you might be able
to get out of your service

24:37.810 --> 24:38.894
if there's no one else
to look‐‐

24:38.936 --> 24:40.229
No, I can't do that.

24:40.270 --> 24:41.605
What?
Why not?

24:41.647 --> 24:42.815
That‐‐
that would be perfect.

24:42.856 --> 24:44.817
It's out of the question, Matt.
We're not done over there yet.

24:44.817 --> 24:45.693
But, Dad, it's grandma‐‐

24:45.734 --> 24:47.903
I'm not gonna argue
about it with you.

24:47.945 --> 24:49.780
We all have to make
sacrifices.

24:49.822 --> 24:50.948
I know, I underst‐‐

24:50.990 --> 24:52.032
Stop, Matt.

24:53.283 --> 24:54.243
Thank you.

24:54.284 --> 24:56.161
