relate to you?

25:48.005 --> 25:49.214
Go.

25:49.214 --> 25:51.675
I don't know.

25:51.717 --> 25:53.177
You don't‐‐
[laughs]

25:53.218 --> 25:55.679
Okay, we just got done
discussing this whole thing.

25:55.721 --> 25:57.806
That was talking.
This is different.

25:57.848 --> 26:00.350
How is this different?
This is the same exact thing.

26:00.392 --> 26:01.226
Just tell me what you‐‐

26:01.268 --> 26:03.979
Seriously, what do you
want me to say?

26:04.021 --> 26:06.023
You know, why don't you
just do it for me?

26:06.065 --> 26:08.567
Just do it for you?
Yeah.

26:08.609 --> 26:09.985
No, I'm not gonna
just do it for you.

26:10.027 --> 26:11.111
I mean‐‐
[stammers]

26:12.237 --> 26:13.906
My God, you really
are ridiculous.

26:13.947 --> 26:15.991
Do you just have the Rally
Girls do everything for you?

26:16.033 --> 26:17.576
I mean, do they
just chew your food

26:17.618 --> 26:20.245
and wipe your butt for you‐‐
how does this work?

26:20.287 --> 26:22.956
I just sat here
and read the entire‐‐

26:22.998 --> 26:24.958
the entire book to you,

26:24.958 --> 26:26.251
and you have nothing to say.

26:26.293 --> 26:28.253
There's gotta be something
in this head of yours

26:28.295 --> 26:29.254
that you can relate to.

26:29.296 --> 26:30.714
I don't know.

26:30.756 --> 26:32.091
There's gotta be something!
I don't know.

26:32.132 --> 26:34.593
What don't you know?
Okay, listen‐‐listen.

26:34.593 --> 26:36.929
Okay, this‐‐this is a book

26:36.929 --> 26:38.847
about two best friends

26:38.889 --> 26:41.600
who have a dream
that gets crushed.

26:41.600 --> 26:43.894
They have a dream
that gets crushed.

26:43.936 --> 26:46.355
You can't tell me that
there's not something

26:46.396 --> 26:48.398
in this head of yours
that you can relate this to.

26:48.440 --> 26:49.900
There's gotta be something!

26:49.942 --> 26:51.610
My Go‐‐

26:51.652 --> 26:54.404
You know, here's an example
how I can relate to this.

26:54.446 --> 26:57.950
I would really, really
like to shoot you right now.

26:57.950 --> 26:59.618
Okay, so you know what?

26:59.660 --> 27:00.619
Just take the book,
and I'm done.

27:00.661 --> 27:03.122
You can figure it out
on your own from here.

27:07.126 --> 27:08.335
[doorbell rings]

27:10.838 --> 27:11.755
Jason.
Hey, Mrs. Taylor.

27:11.797 --> 27:14.091
How are you, honey?
I'm good, I'm good.

27:14.133 --> 27:16.426
Um, how are you?
I'm good.

27:16.468 --> 27:18.428
Did you wheel yourself
all the way over here?

27:18.470 --> 27:19.805
Yeah, I did.

27:19.805 --> 27:22.432
It's no big deal.
I do it all the time.

27:22.474 --> 27:24.893
Oh, my‐‐well,
did you want to see Coach?

27:24.935 --> 27:26.895
He's not here.
He's at a meeting.

27:26.937 --> 27:29.439
And then we got
this church dinner.

27:29.481 --> 27:31.441
Um, well, you know what?
Come on inside.

27:31.483 --> 27:34.945
You know what?
I was just thinking about you.

27:34.987 --> 27:37.447
I was just thinking about
when you might

27:37.489 --> 27:40.158
feel like you're ready
to go back to school.

27:41.660 --> 27:42.995
I, uh,

27:42.995 --> 27:45.372
I haven't really
thought about it yet.

27:45.414 --> 27:48.709
Just keep in mind that you can
come back any time you want.

27:48.709 --> 27:50.419
I mean, you don't have to,
you know,

27:50.460 --> 27:52.963
wait for the new semester
or anything like that.

27:53.005 --> 27:54.673
I know.

27:54.673 --> 27:55.924
You've practically
got all your courses

27:55.966 --> 27:57.968
taken care of anyway.

27:58.010 --> 28:00.137
You've only got
a few credits left.

28:00.178 --> 28:02.014
Yeah, just, I'm‐‐

28:02.014 --> 28:05.767
I don't know if I'm ready
to be part of the, uh,

28:05.809 --> 28:09.104
Dillon High rumor mill
right now.

28:09.146 --> 28:11.023
I got enough to handle.

28:11.064 --> 28:13.984
Are you talking about
that thing with Lyla?

28:14.026 --> 28:16.695
I'm just so confused,
you know.

28:16.695 --> 28:18.822
It's just‐‐

28:20.365 --> 28:22.367
I saw Lyla the other day,

28:22.367 --> 28:23.994
and we just‐‐

28:24.036 --> 28:25.829
Don't tell Coach, please.

28:25.871 --> 28:27.372
Oh, no.
I won't.

28:27.414 --> 28:29.750
We kinda, sorta

28:29.791 --> 28:32.002
tried to get back
together, and‐‐

28:34.212 --> 28:36.006
I want to.
I just want to, you know?

28:36.048 --> 28:38.717
But I'm just having
such a hard time with it.

28:38.717 --> 28:39.843
It's just‐‐

28:39.885 --> 28:41.720
It's just‐‐it's Lyla.

28:41.720 --> 28:42.971
I wish it was someone else.

28:43.013 --> 28:44.848
I wish it was someone
different.

28:44.890 --> 28:46.975
I wish I could just hate her
and walk away from it

28:47.017 --> 28:49.770
and be done with it, 'cause
it would be so much easier.

28:51.063 --> 28:52.189
Be a lot easier.

28:52.230 --> 28:54.066
But I love her, you know?
And‐‐

28:56.902 --> 28:58.820
We were gonna get married.

28:58.862 --> 28:59.905
Mm.

28:59.905 --> 29:01.239
That's a hard thing.

29:01.239 --> 29:03.784
It's a hard, hard thing.

29:06.078 --> 29:08.246
But I will say

29:08.288 --> 29:11.959
there's no weakness
in forgiveness.

29:13.293 --> 29:15.087
If that's what you decide.

29:29.893 --> 29:31.770
Look what I found.

29:31.770 --> 29:34.356
Your mom gave it to me
about a hundred years ago.

29:34.398 --> 29:35.941
You want it?

29:35.941 --> 29:37.734
Sure.

29:38.735 --> 29:39.903
Thanks.

29:45.784 --> 29:48.203
Talked to your Aunt Peg
in Oklahoma,

29:48.245 --> 29:51.623
and she said she's willing
to have you live with her.

29:53.667 --> 29:55.043
You don't have to do that.

29:55.085 --> 29:57.796
I can stay here
and take care of grandma

29:57.838 --> 30:00.382
just like I‐‐
just like I've been doing.

30:00.424 --> 30:02.718
Something's gotta be done,
all right?

30:02.759 --> 30:03.385
And I found a home for her.

30:03.427 --> 30:05.637
Grandma's not even‐‐she's‐‐

30:05.679 --> 30:07.806
She won't even know
anyone there.

30:07.806 --> 30:10.976
Matt, look,

30:11.018 --> 30:12.811
I know this ain't easy.

30:12.811 --> 30:14.146
All right?
Let me help you with that.

30:14.187 --> 30:15.397
It's fine.

30:15.439 --> 30:16.398
Let me help you.
I'm gonna be late.

30:16.440 --> 30:18.608
I just gotta go, okay?

30:20.444 --> 30:21.653
[door closes]

30:21.653 --> 30:23.238
(reverend)
Let us pray.

30:23.280 --> 30:26.074
Dear Lord,
our heavenly Father,

30:26.116 --> 30:28.660
we ask that you give
these boys

30:28.702 --> 30:31.455
the strength
to be guided by you

30:31.496 --> 30:35.042
and to be vessels
for your saving message.

30:35.042 --> 30:38.170
And to play with the passion

30:38.170 --> 30:40.839
that you yourself
have blessed them with.

30:40.839 --> 30:41.840
Amen.

30:41.840 --> 30:43.008
(worshippers)
Amen.

30:43.008 --> 30:44.676
Let's have some barbecue.

30:44.676 --> 30:47.345
[country western music]

30:47.387 --> 30:49.431
(Taylor)
Hey.

30:49.473 --> 30:51.016
(Riggins)
Coach.

30:51.016 --> 30:53.018
(Taylor)
I don't give you
the impression

30:53.018 --> 30:55.687
that I think of you as only
a football player, do I?

30:55.729 --> 30:58.190
I bring this up because,
as usual,

30:58.231 --> 31:00.776
my wife is always right.

31:00.817 --> 31:02.861
You got your midterms
comin' up.

31:02.861 --> 31:05.197
I'm gonna be in contact
with your teachers.

31:05.197 --> 31:07.115
I'm gonna know
what's goin' on.

31:07.157 --> 31:09.034
There are gonna be
no more free rides.

31:09.076 --> 31:11.411
You're gonna start
paying.

31:12.704 --> 31:15.749
And hear me
when I say this.

31:15.791 --> 31:18.210
No pass...

31:18.251 --> 31:20.337
no play.

31:22.255 --> 31:24.382
So, uh,
where's your dad?

31:24.424 --> 31:26.384
He's not coming.

31:27.547 --> 31:29.841
But I thought you said
he was gonna come.

31:29.883 --> 31:32.427
Yeah, but he's just
not coming, okay?

31:32.427 --> 31:33.929
He had something to do.

31:33.970 --> 31:35.055
That kinda sucks.

31:35.096 --> 31:36.056
What does he have
that's so impor‐‐
I don't know.

31:36.097 --> 31:39.434
He just had something
that was going on, okay?

31:41.937 --> 31:43.605
Are you okay?
No, I'm not.

31:43.605 --> 31:45.440
And you picking at me's
not helping,

31:45.440 --> 31:47.567
so could we just
not talk about it?

31:48.777 --> 31:51.071
Yeah‐‐yeah, Matt.
Whatever.

32:02.123 --> 32:05.585
[sound of crowd cheering]

32:13.969 --> 32:15.554
(announcer)
Midway through
the third quarter,

32:15.595 --> 32:18.473
Westcott, 24.
Dillon, 14.

32:18.515 --> 32:19.558
(Saracen)
White 40!

32:19.599 --> 32:22.561
White 40!

32:22.602 --> 32:24.563
White 40! Hut!

32:24.604 --> 32:26.481
(announcer)
He drops back.
He's got Dolia!

32:26.481 --> 32:27.732
He's wide open in the flats.

32:27.774 --> 32:31.069
(Coach)
Guys, he's open!
Get him! Get him!

32:31.111 --> 32:33.613
Come on, son.
You gotta get rid of that!

32:35.031 --> 32:37.617
Get up, Son.
Let's go! Get up!

32:37.659 --> 32:41.621
(announcer)
Matt Saracen is just not
on his game tonight, folks.

32:47.961 --> 32:51.006
(announcer)
Oh, it's a bad pitch!

32:51.006 --> 32:52.048
Williams picks it up.

32:52.090 --> 32:54.843
Oh, a nice stiff arm as he
makes it to the outside!

32:54.843 --> 32:55.844
He scoots through!

32:55.844 --> 32:58.847
He's got one man to beat.

32:58.847 --> 33:02.267
Oh! Smash Williams,
touchdown!

33:02.309 --> 33:04.269
Dillon Panthers, touchdown!

33:04.311 --> 33:07.606
Saracen! Come here.

33:07.647 --> 33:08.690
Let me tell you
something.

33:08.690 --> 33:10.859
Let me tell you something‐‐
Smash is out there.

33:10.901 --> 33:13.028
He is covering
for your ass right now.

33:13.028 --> 33:15.697
You better screw your head on
real tight, you understand me?

33:15.697 --> 33:17.699
Yes, Coach.

33:19.910 --> 33:22.662
Come on, you heard him.
Get your head in the game, boy.

33:22.662 --> 33:25.665
(announcer)
Here in the fourth quarter,
Westcott with the ball.

33:26.917 --> 33:27.959
(Taylor)
Hey!

33:28.001 --> 33:29.878
Hey!
That's nice!

33:29.878 --> 33:32.547
(announcer)
And that is gonna bring up
the fourth down.

33:32.589 --> 33:33.715
Dolia, Smash,
come here, come here.

33:33.715 --> 33:35.884
We're going for the block.
We're going for the block.

33:35.926 --> 33:37.302
And I want creeper right.
Creeper right, you understand?

33:37.344 --> 33:38.845
Hey, get there.

33:53.610 --> 33:56.029
(announcer)
And Dillon gets it back.

33:57.697 --> 33:59.240
All right, let's get up
and now let's go.

33:59.282 --> 34:00.617
Capitalize right here.

34:00.617 --> 34:02.702
Time to capitalize, baby.
Come on.

34:02.744 --> 34:05.580
(Smash)
Hey, get on your feet
and make some noise!

34:05.580 --> 34:08.333
Get up and make some noise!

34:08.375 --> 34:11.086
Hey, listen, they press their
cornerback tight on first down.

34:11.086 --> 34:12.087
I wanna go deep.

34:12.087 --> 34:14.172
One big play wipes away
all the little mistakes.

34:14.214 --> 34:15.840
We walk outta here winners.
Do you understand me?

34:15.882 --> 34:18.009
Yes, sir.
What's the call?

34:18.051 --> 34:19.260
Pro gun right,
X, Y cross.

34:19.260 --> 34:20.595
Got it?
And let it fly.

34:20.595 --> 34:21.888
Throw it long,
you understand?

34:21.930 --> 34:24.099
Do, it, Matt. Make something
happen, baby! Come on!

34:24.099 --> 34:26.601
(announcer)
And here comes Matt Saracen
back onto the field,

34:26.601 --> 34:28.186
with plenty of time
here in the fourth quarter

34:28.228 --> 34:30.730
to get his team
back into this.

34:33.274 --> 34:35.944
Green 12!

34:38.655 --> 34:39.739
Hut!

34:42.200 --> 34:45.662
(announcer)
Oh! The safety
is out of position.

34:45.662 --> 34:47.789
Williams streaking up
the sideline.

34:47.789 --> 34:50.667
Matt Saracen
lets it fly!

34:55.130 --> 34:57.716
Oh, no! No!

34:57.757 --> 35:01.636
He just overthrew
Smash Williams by a mile.

35:01.636 --> 35:04.723
That could have been
an easy touchdown for Dillon.

35:04.764 --> 35:05.890
Start warming up Weston.

35:05.932 --> 35:08.226
Weston, let's go!
Warm it up.

35:08.268 --> 35:09.728
Time!
Time!

35:09.769 --> 35:10.729
[whistle blows]

35:10.770 --> 35:12.814
Get off the field, boys!

35:12.856 --> 35:15.066
Step out.
It's not your night, son.

35:15.108 --> 35:17.944
Come on,
shake it off!

35:19.112 --> 35:20.655
All right, get out there.

35:20.655 --> 35:22.157
Get in there.
Take over.

35:22.157 --> 35:24.117
(announcer)
Coach Taylor's
benched Matt Saracen

35:24.159 --> 35:25.869
and is sending in

35:25.869 --> 35:28.830
his second string
quarterback Brett Weston.

35:28.830 --> 35:30.999
Now this might be
a risky move,

35:30.999 --> 35:33.752
but the way Saracen
has played tonight, folks,

35:33.793 --> 35:35.628
what does Coach Taylor
have to lose?

36:13.833 --> 36:15.335
There you go!

36:19.839 --> 36:21.424
(Taylor)
There you go!

36:28.390 --> 36:30.141
(man)
Good game, Coach.

36:30.183 --> 36:31.434
Very good.
Yes, sir!

36:42.028 --> 36:44.489
You'll get 'em
next time, Matt.

36:44.531 --> 36:46.950
You're sending me
to Oklahoma.

36:46.950 --> 36:48.785
You can play football
anywhere.

36:48.785 --> 36:51.162
Go to hell, Dad.

36:51.204 --> 36:53.331
What'd you say?
I said go to hell.

36:53.373 --> 36:54.833
Matt, just get in the truck
right now, and we'll talk‐‐

36:54.874 --> 36:56.084
I'm not getting
in the truck with you,

36:56.084 --> 36:57.252
and I'm not gonna
go home with you.

36:57.252 --> 36:59.254
You know, I thought you were
gonna come home from Iraq

36:59.254 --> 37:00.255
and actually be able to help,

37:00.296 --> 37:01.840
but you've
only made things worse.

37:01.881 --> 37:03.425
Do you know what?

37:03.425 --> 37:05.343
Actually, why don't you
just go back to Iraq?

37:05.385 --> 37:08.012
'Cause things worked out a lot
better when you were there.

37:08.054 --> 37:09.347
Really, you calling me
all the time‐‐"Help me.

37:09.389 --> 37:10.432
"Grandma
can't do anything right.

37:10.432 --> 37:12.350
I don't know what to do.
I don't know what to do."

37:12.392 --> 37:14.185
I'm sorry‐‐it's hard to pay the
rent and go to school and take‐‐

37:14.227 --> 37:15.437
Try being me
for five minutes!

37:15.478 --> 37:16.312
Try being you?
What have you done?

37:16.354 --> 37:17.730
You think I wanna
come home to this?

37:17.772 --> 37:20.775
Now get in the truck.
I'm not going anywhere
with you.

37:20.775 --> 37:22.110
Get in the truck.
You get in the truck.

37:22.152 --> 37:23.445
Where you gonna go?

37:23.486 --> 37:25.405
I don't know.

37:26.781 --> 37:29.117
Let me know
when you go back to Iraq.

37:30.869 --> 37:33.788
Let's go to our house.
Come on, you, let's go.

37:33.788 --> 37:35.457
Come on.

37:35.457 --> 37:36.742
It's okay,
it's okay, it's okay.

37:39.794 --> 37:42.797
[heavy metal]

37:42.797 --> 37:46.301
[indistinct lyrics]

37:46.301 --> 37:48.136
♪ You can count on
your son ♪

37:48.136 --> 37:50.305
[screaming indistinctly]

37:50.305 --> 37:57.145
♪ You don't stand
right by my side ♪

37:57.145 --> 38:02.150
[screaming lyrics]

38:02.150 --> 38:05.403
[music stops]

38:12.869 --> 38:15.079
Lookee here.

38:15.121 --> 38:16.664
Wow.

38:16.664 --> 38:17.665
[chuckles]

38:17.665 --> 38:19.834
What do you think?

38:19.834 --> 38:21.836
That's some
intense stuff, man.

38:21.836 --> 38:23.338
Very intense.

38:23.338 --> 38:26.424
Showed up.
Didn't think you would.

38:26.466 --> 38:28.176
You wanna know why?

38:28.176 --> 38:29.260
Why?

38:30.512 --> 38:32.680
'Cause you're looking at
a B‐.

38:32.680 --> 38:33.431
You got a B‐?

38:33.473 --> 38:35.099
Not too shabby, huh?
There you go.

38:35.141 --> 38:37.352
Look at you, turning into
a scholar on me.

38:37.352 --> 38:40.188
I appreciate your help, man.
I really do.

38:40.188 --> 38:41.689
And,

38:41.689 --> 38:43.775
I'm sorry I just caught
the last bit of your, uh,

38:43.816 --> 38:44.859
set there, so‐‐

38:44.859 --> 38:46.444
No, no, no, don't worry.

38:46.486 --> 38:48.112
We got a whole 'nother set
coming up, so‐‐

38:48.154 --> 38:50.365
No worries, my friend,
we'll put you‐‐

38:50.365 --> 38:51.449
you know, you're with me,

38:51.491 --> 38:53.910
so we'll put you right
up here at the front, okay?

38:53.910 --> 38:54.661
That's great.

38:54.702 --> 38:56.829
You can't just
stand there, though.

38:56.871 --> 38:59.499
You gotta‐‐
You gotta do that a lot.

39:17.684 --> 39:19.852
(Street)
You're incredibly stealthy.

39:19.894 --> 39:21.396
[giggles]

39:21.396 --> 39:24.399
You could be like
a glamorous jewel thief.
Shut up.

39:24.399 --> 39:26.859
You could go into breaking
and entering for a living.

39:32.740 --> 39:34.450
What are you
doing here, Lyla?

39:34.450 --> 39:36.869
Can't seem to kick
the habit.

39:36.911 --> 39:37.870
[laughs]

39:51.926 --> 39:54.178
If it's gonna end
between us,

39:54.220 --> 39:57.432
I guess
I can't help that.

39:57.432 --> 40:00.184
But...

40:00.226 --> 40:03.229
it can't end the way
it did the other night.

40:07.442 --> 40:10.695
I just wanted to be close
to you again, Jason.

40:11.738 --> 40:14.198
I'm trying, Lyla.

40:14.240 --> 40:17.285
I really am.

40:25.460 --> 40:28.254
I love you.

40:29.631 --> 40:31.758
I know.

40:37.263 --> 40:38.806
(Tami)
Hey.

40:38.806 --> 40:41.517
What are you doing?

40:44.646 --> 40:47.273
I just don't
want him to go.

40:51.986 --> 40:55.281
Come on.
Let's get ready for bed.

40:58.034 --> 41:00.620
That's it.

41:00.662 --> 41:03.831
Grandma's going into a home,
and I'm going to Oklahoma.

41:03.831 --> 41:06.292
Do you want me
to talk to him?

41:06.334 --> 41:09.587
I'll talk to him, see if
we can work something out.

41:10.838 --> 41:13.466
Nothing to work out.

41:13.508 --> 41:15.677
Listen to me.
We're all family here.

41:15.677 --> 41:18.971
I'll do anything I can for you.
You know that.

41:19.013 --> 41:20.306
Hell, Buddy Garrity,

41:20.348 --> 41:22.517
he ain't gonna let you
cross the state line

41:22.517 --> 41:23.976
without finishing
this season.

41:24.018 --> 41:26.312
He'll call out the damn
national guard if he has to.

41:28.022 --> 41:29.816
I hate him.

41:31.359 --> 41:33.403
I hate my dad.

41:35.530 --> 41:38.533
Hey, don't do that.

41:38.533 --> 41:40.868
Don't make that mistake.

41:42.704 --> 41:44.038
You think about
what you just said.

41:44.038 --> 41:45.456
You get ready to go,
come inside.

41:45.498 --> 41:46.958
I'll take you home.

42:42.430 --> 43:25.014
